25 d. A party referred to in sub-subdivision (7)d. of this section.
26 "§ 64-65. Prohibited foreign party ownership of data centers and land on which a data
27 center is located.
28 (a) Notwithstanding any provision of law to the contrary, no adversarial nation shall
29 either:
30 (1) Purchase, acquire, lease, or hold any interest in land on which a data center is
31 located.
32 (2) Have any significant interest in or substantial control of a data center.
33 (b) Except as provided in this section, a prohibited foreign party shall not acquire by
34 grant, purchase, devise, descent, or otherwise any interest, other than a de minimis direct interest,
35 in land described in subsection (a) of this section or a data center in this State. A party may not
36 knowingly hold land, or a significant interest in or substantial control of a data center, as an agent,
37 trustee, or other fiduciary for a prohibited foreign party in violation of this section. A prohibited
38 foreign party that acquires land, or holds a significant interest in or substantial control of a data
39 center, in violation of this section remains in violation as long as the prohibited foreign party
40 holds an interest in the land, or the significant interest in or substantial control of a data center.
41 A prohibited foreign party who is a resident alien of the United States shall have the right to
42 acquire and hold land described in subsection (a) of this section, or a significant interest in or
43 substantial control of a data center, in the State upon the same terms as a citizen of the United
44 States during the continuance of the party's residence in this State.
45 (c) A prohibited foreign party that has acquired any interest in land described in
46 subsection (a) of this section, or a significant interest in or substantial control of a data center, in
47 this State prior to the effective date of this section may continue to own or hold that interest but
48 may not acquire by grant, purchase, devise, descent, or otherwise any additional interest in land
49 described in subsection (a) of this section, or a significant interest in or substantial control of a
50 data center, in this State and must register with the Secretary of State and the Attorney General.
51 The Secretary of State and the Attorney General shall maintain one joint database of those foreign
Page 4 Senate Bill 730-Fourth Edition

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 parties that have registered, and the database shall be accessible and searchable by the public on
2 each agency's website. The Secretary of State and the Attorney General shall establish a
3 registration form for the purposes of this subsection, and the form shall include at least the
4 following information:
5 (1) The name of the owner of the land or the owner of the interest in the land, or
6 the owner of the data center, as applicable.
7 (2) The address of the land, the parcel identification number, and the property's
8 legal description, or the address of the data center, as applicable.
9 (3) The number of acres of the land on which the data center is located.
10 (4) The mailing address of the owner of the land or the data center, as applicable.
11 (5) Country of citizenship and residency status or country of incorporation of the
12 owner of the land or the owner of the interest in the land, or the owner of the
13 data center, as applicable.
14 (d) A prohibited foreign party that fails to timely file a registration with the Secretary of
15 State and the Attorney General pursuant to subsection (c) of this section is subject to a civil
16 penalty of not less than one thousand dollars ($1,000) for each day that the registration is late,
17 the clear proceeds of which shall be remitted to the Civil Penalty and Forfeiture Fund, in
18 accordance with G.S. 115C-457.2. The unpaid balance of any penalties assessed under this
19 subsection shall constitute a lien against the land if a lien, denoted as a Notice of Foreign
20 Ownership Violation Lien, has been recorded by the Attorney General in the office of the register
21 of deeds in the county where the property is located, and the lien shall have priority from the date
22 and time of recordation and shall be enforced by the Attorney General.
23 (e) A prohibited foreign party that acquires land described in subsection (a) of this
24 section, or a significant interest in or substantial control of a data center, on or after the effective
25 date of this section, by devise or descent, through the enforcement of security interests, or through
26 the collection of debts, other than a de minimis direct interest, shall sell, transfer, or otherwise
27 divest itself of the land within three years after acquiring the land, or the significant interest in or
28 substantial control of the data center.
29 (f) At the time of purchase, a buyer of any interest in land described in subsection (a) of
30 this section shall provide an affidavit signed under penalty of perjury attesting that the buyer is
31 (i) not a prohibited foreign party and (ii) in compliance with the requirements of this section. The
32 affidavit is not required to be notarized and shall be attached as an exhibit to the deed or other
33 document that conveys an ownership interest in the land. The failure to obtain or maintain the
34 affidavit shall not affect the title or insurability of the title for the land, and shall not result in civil
35 or criminal liability to any person or entity, unless the person or entity is in violation of subsection
36 (k) of this section herein, or subject any nonparty to the purchase to civil or criminal liability,
37 unless a nonparty to the purchase has actual knowledge that the transaction will result in a
38 violation of this section. The Real Estate Commission shall establish the form for the affidavit
39 required under this subsection.
40 (g) Upon receipt of information that leads the Attorney General to believe that a
41 prohibited foreign party has not divested itself of the land described in subsection (a) of this
42 section, or a significant interest in or substantial control of a data center, as required under
43 subsection (e) of this section, the Attorney General shall enforce a violation of this section by
44 commencing a receivership proceeding in the county where the property or data center is situated
45 under Article 38A of Chapter 1 of the General Statutes seeking the appointment of a general
46 receiver pursuant to G.S. 1-507.24(e1). Any interest in real property acquired or held in violation
47 of this section shall be subject to divestiture pursuant to G.S. 64-66.
48 (h) A violation of this section by an adversarial nation may, at the discretion of the
49 noteholder, be deemed a default under a loan, mortgage, or deed of trust and shall provide the
50 lender the automatic right to trigger default on the loan, mortgage, or deed of trust.
