1 (d) As used in this section, the term "data center" means a facility, campus of facilities,
2 or array of interconnected facilities used by an entity or other business enterprise for the primary
3 purpose of storing, retrieving, managing, and processing digital data, which has a peak monthly
4 electricity demand of 100 megawatts or greater.
5 (e) The Commission may adopt rules to implement the requirements of this section.
6 Nothing in this section shall be construed to limit the authority of the Commission to adopt such
7 additional rules as are in the public interest to protect retail customers from costs incurred by
8 electric public utilities to provide electric service to data centers."
9 SECTION 4.(b) This section is effective when it becomes law and applies to
10 agreements between an electric public utility and a data center entered into on or after that date.
