12 NO CONDEMNATION FOR DATA CENTERS
13 SECTION 5. Article 1 of Chapter 40A of the General Statutes is amended by adding
14 a new section to read:
15 "§ 40A-14. No condemnation to facilitate siting of data center.
16 Notwithstanding any authority granted under this Chapter, no condemnor shall exercise the
17 power of eminent domain for the purpose of acquiring land for a data center to be sited upon."
18
19 NO LOCAL GOVERNMENT INCENTIVES FOR DATA CENTERS
20 SECTION 6.(a) G.S. 158-7.1 is amended by adding a new subsection to read:
21 "(i) Notwithstanding subsection (a), (b), or (d) of this section, local governments are
22 prohibited from providing any economic development incentives for siting of a data center within
23 their jurisdiction. For purposes of this section, the term "data center" means a facility, campus of
24 facilities, or array of interconnected facilities used by an entity or other business enterprise for
25 the primary purpose of storing, retrieving, managing, and processing digital data, which has a
26 peak monthly electricity demand of 100 megawatts or greater."
27 SECTION 6.(b) This section is effective when it becomes law and applies to data
28 centers for which no local development approvals or State permits, certifications, or
29 authorizations have been issued for siting of the data center on or before that date. This section
30 shall not be construed to impair agreements for incentives executed on or before that date.
